The paper discusses alternative metrics in scientometrics, which involves the use of digital tools and methods to study scientific publications and their impact. The paper specifically focuses on three altmetrics: microblogging (Twitter), online reference managers (Mendeley and CiteULike), and blogging. These altmetrics are commonly used in the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL), social media (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), social networks (cs.SOC), and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
